---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="The Guide" active="guide">
  <div class="part-head">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="kicker">Under construction, deliberately</p>
      <h1>The guide</h1>
      <p class="lede prose">Scene-by-scene guides to the play, the characters and their arcs, key quotations, and clear guidance on the Shakespeare coursework assignment. This site is growing: the framework is here, and the guides arrive as the unit is taught.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <section class="band">
    <div class="wrap prose">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0;">Planned contents</h2>
      <ul class="tick">
        <li>Act-by-act, scene-by-scene guides with staging and language analysis</li>
        <li>Character studies: the Macbeths, Banquo, Duncan, Macduff, the Witches</li>
        <li>A quotation bank with act, scene and line references</li>
        <li>Context that earns its place: kingship, the supernatural, James I</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Each guide follows the family method: what the text or form is doing, the methods that
      matter, and analysis that always moves from device to effect.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
